   <h1>The Troll&#39;s Bane Chronicle</h1>

   <h2>The fifth year of the new era: October</h2>

<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 1st of October, Revlen goads the Lich creature Dravish into contacting him. It remains unknown as to whether or not Revlen ever met with him.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 2nd of October, the girl Rhiannon implores the town to show her father and Captain of the Town Guard, Pendar Fayed, respect. </p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 2nd of October, the town guard Callith announces that he intends to combat the threat of Dravish with an army. He declares that he seeks to recruit anyone with proficiency in weaponry.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 3rd of October, the town guard Revlen places a ban on the man Dei. The elf, and fellow town guard Callith reminds him that as but a recruit, this ability is not yet his.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 3rd of October, the dwarf Xantor announces his intention the depart on an expidition with his fellow dwarves.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 8th of October, Elliot Stewborne, Page to the Duke of Machyllyneth announces that a crafting event previously announced has been cancelled. The population show little regret and Mr Stewborne is never seen again.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 10th of October, Revlen falls to the continued onslaught of the lich Dravish.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 10th of October, Pendar remains afflicted by Dravish's recent assaults. His family and friends gather around him in the inn to wish him well health.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 10th of October, To deal with the current crisis in relation to Dravish, the monk of Eldan, Falk vom Wald announces that he is selling many items at reasonable prices. There is general interest from the town and most of his goods are purchased.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 10th of October, Callith, the current leader of the town-guard in Pendar's absence, calls all guards to his side to deal with the current crisis. Farel, a former town-guard godes Callith into an argument, but another town-guard, Culandria diffuses the situation. </p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 12th of October, Alfred Corvane, a recruit of the town-guard warns everybody that the dwarf Draxin Bluebeard has attacked several people, including the Earl of the Grey Rose, Lennier, Alexander von Hattingen and several others who remain un-named. Corvane later announces that he has killed the dwarf, much to the outrage of the lizard Xalliar. It is revealed by the lizard that Corvane, in an act of brutality pierced the dwarf's head upon a spike outside of the Castle of the Grey Rose. The Knight of the Rose, Marius Eisenhauer ends the dispute, stating that in future, no town-guard has any jurisdiction within the walls of the castle. Corvane remains a guard.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 13th of October, Arthur Swallow announces his interest in learning more about the gods of the world. Brother Markous, Aragon ben Galwan, Allersheim of Adron and several others offer to teach him and all others interested the legends and stories of the gods.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 16th of October, the human Kevin Lightdot returns from a long absence. He is welcomed back by the town-guard Culandria.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 16th of October, Rogan Silverbeard offers an apology to the un-named elf that he assaulted in Eliza's shop.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 20th of October, Faladron Furnir offers a reward for the safe return of  his bethrothed, Marie Tolong's,  golden ring.
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 22nd of October, Moirear Sian encounters severla beholders on his way to Troll's Bane from Greenbriar. He offers, on the behalf of all Varshikari, to protect this stretch of land from all foul beasts. </p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, around the 23rd of October, a discussion is had about the planting of trees by the Pillar of the Vorkalion. It is encouraged that none do this, for their own protection from the dark forces at work in the area.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 25th of October, Kamik Windslasher, a mercenary, offers his services to all those who hold an interest.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 26th of October, Aragon ben Galwan expresses disappointment towards the new citizenship list of Troll's Bane. He states that he is not impressed with the decision by Pendar Fayed and others to omit several important person's names.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 26th of October, Troll's Bane Training Academy is established with the aim to train soldiers in the ways of war and combat.</p>
<p>In the 5th year of the new age, on the 30th of October, a cryptic message is left upon the wall: "The 13th will come.. we will take your homes.. your food..and your lives until it is done. "</p>

